cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CY, cs.SE, cs.LG 

The paper discusses the design and security analysis of a new family of stream ciphers, which falls under the category of cryptography and security. Therefore, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of non-volatile FPGA devices and lightweight identification protocols, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) respectively. The paper also discusses the potential use of these stream ciphers in self-reconfiguring SoC non-volatile FPGAs, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
